Kyrle Bellew https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kyrle_Bellew 0 Harold Kyrle Money Bellew (28 March 1850 – 2 November 1911), better known as Kyrle Bellew, was an English stage and silent film actor. He notably toured with Cora Brown-Potter in the 1880s and 1890s, and was cast as the leading man in many stage productions alongside her. He was also a signwriter, gold prospector and rancher mainly in Australia.
